  "local_port": 47856,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Where can I get audiobooks for free in English?",
  "response": "There are numerous legitimate sources where you can access free English audiobooks. Below is a comprehensive list of platforms and services that offer a wide range of titles across various genres:\n\n### 1. **LibriVox**\n- **Website:** [librivox.org](https://librivox.org/)\n- **Description:** LibriVox offers over 24,000 free public domain audiobooks read by a community of volunteers. It's an excellent resource for classic literature.\n\n### 2. **Project Gutenberg**\n- **Website:** [gutenberg.org](https://www.gutenberg.org/)\n- **Description:** While primarily known for its vast collection of free eBooks, Project Gutenberg also provides a selection of human-read and computer-generated audiobooks.\n\n### 3. **Open Culture**\n- **Website:** [openculture.com/freeaudiobooks](http://www.openculture.com/freeaudiobooks)\n- **Description:** Open Culture curates a list of free audiobooks from various sources, including classics and contemporary works, available for download or streaming.\n\n### 4. **Lit2Go**\n- **Website:** [etc.usf.edu/lit2go](https://etc.usf.edu/lit2go/)\n- **Description:** Hosted by the University of South Florida, Lit2Go offers free audiobooks, poems, and short stories, complete with accompanying texts and educational materials.\n\n### 5. **Loyal Books**\n- **Website:** [loyalbooks.com](http://www.loyalbooks.com/)\n- **Description:** Previously known as \"Books Should Be Free,\" Loyal Books provides free public domain audiobooks categorized by genre and language.\n\n### 6. **Internet Archive**\n- **Website:** [archive.org/details/audio_bookspoetry](https://archive.org/details/audio_bookspoetry)\n- **Description:** The Internet Archive hosts a vast library of audiobooks and poetry recordings, including both public domain and contemporary works.\n\n### 7. **Your Local Library**\n- **Services:** **OverDrive/Libby**, **Hoopla**\n- **Description:** Many public libraries offer free access to audiobooks through digital lending services like OverDrive (accessed via the Libby app) and Hoopla. All you need is a valid library card.\n  - **OverDrive/Libby:** [libbyapp.com](https://libbyapp.com/)\n  - **Hoopla:** [hoopladigital.com](https://www.hoopladigital.com/)\n\n### 8. **Spotify**\n- **Website:** [spotify.com](https://www.spotify.com/)\n- **Description:** While primarily a music streaming service, Spotify hosts a selection of free audiobooks. Availability may vary, and some content may include advertisements.\n\n### 9. **YouTube**\n- **Website:** [youtube.com](https://www.youtube.com/)\n- **Description:** Many audiobooks, especially those in the public domain, are available for free on YouTube. Simply search for the book title followed by \"audiobook.\"\n\n### 10. **Audiobook Treasury Free Section**\n- **Website:** [audiobooktreasury.com/free-audiobooks](https://audiobooktreasury.com/free-audiobooks/)\n- **Description:** Offers a curated list of free audiobooks across various genres, including classics and contemporary titles.\n\n### 11. **Storynory**\n- **Website:** [storynory.com](https://www.storynory.com/)\n- **Description:** Ideal for younger audiences, Storynory provides free audiobooks of fairy tales, original stories, and educational content.\n\n### 12. **Podcasts and Specialized Apps**\n- **Examples:**\n  - **Podfic Library:** [podfic.com](https://podfic.com/)\n  - **Audiobooks.com Free Section:** Occasionally offers free titles.\n- **Description:** Some podcasts and specialized audiobook apps offer free chapters or complete books as part of their content.\n\n### **Points to Consider:**\n- **Public Domain vs. Contemporary Works:** Most free audiobook resources focus on public domain titles. Access to contemporary audiobooks may require subscriptions or may be limited to library services.\n- **Quality and Narration:** Volunteer-read audiobooks (e.g., LibriVox) vary in narration quality. Professional narrations are typically found in paid services.\n- **Legal and Ethical Use:** Always ensure you're accessing audiobooks from legitimate sources to respect copyright laws and support authors.\n\n### **Bonus: Free Trials on Premium Services**\nIf you're open to trying premium services, many offer free trials that include access to a selection of audiobooks:\n- **Audible:** [audible.com](https://www.audible.com/) offers a 30-day free trial with one or more free audiobooks.\n- **Scribd:** [scribd.com](https://www.scribd.com/) provides a 30-day free trial granting access to unlimited audiobooks, eBooks, and more.\n\n**Note:** Remember to cancel before the trial period ends if you do not wish to incur charges.\n\n---\n\nBy exploring these resources, you should be able to find a wide array of free English audiobooks to suit your interests and needs.",
